<br>
I have been in a situation like this, and I have to admit, it's not fun. As another character, I was stuck between two people I was guilded with who were playing the same class as me, at the same season. Both of them had bought platinum and powerlevelled up to my season, which was fine and all, but because of this they didn't know how to play their class particularly well. I had taken a long time levelling, and knew the class backwards. I was good at it, and enjoyed the class a great deal.<br>
<br>
However, because the two people I was stuck between were so ridiculously well-geared, it didn't matter that I was better at my class. They were much harder to kill because they had more HPs, and therefore were more desirable in a group. I became downhearted, and began to spend a lot of time soloing, which was neither easy nor fun for that particular class. Eventually I gave up the character altogether and rerolled as a different class, which I played for a few months before I realised that I just missed the old one too much and restored her. Now the two people I was stuck between are higher-levelled and don't play as much, so it's less of an issue. <br>
<br>
I am not particularly rabid about people buying platinum and ebaying characters and so forth, but to say that it doesn't have an effect on anyone else is a little inaccurate. I'm not getting the violins out or anything, but yeah, it made me sad.<br>
<br>
